00:00:16,828 --> 00:00:19,069
I think it's kinda hard to do.

6
00:00:19,069 --> 00:00:21,410
But I am a big fan of a quote by Alan Kay,

7
00:00:21,410 --> 00:00:25,932
which is the best way to predict the future is to invent it.

8
00:00:26,927 --> 00:00:28,248
or to build it.

9
00:00:28,248 --> 00:00:30,890
And so, I think what we're gonna do today is,

10
00:00:30,890 --> 00:00:33,973
we're gonna talk a little bit about our learnings

11
00:00:33,973 --> 00:00:37,796
at Niantic, having launched some AR products

12
00:00:37,796 --> 00:00:40,138
and run them over the past couple of years.

13
00:00:40,138 --> 00:00:43,161
And then, I'm gonna share some about our thoughts

14
00:00:43,161 --> 00:00:45,363
about stuff that's under development right now.

15
00:00:45,363 --> 00:00:47,124
So, stage one's looking back,

16
00:00:47,124 --> 00:00:49,326
stage two's about what tech is getting built

17
00:00:49,326 --> 00:00:50,407
and the importance of that tech.

18
00:00:51,128 --> 00:00:55,171
And then stage three of the talk is going to be about what we think the implications

19
00:00:55,171 --> 00:01:00,214
of that technology are for the kinds of products that we can build, whether they're games,

