00:50:27,964 --> 00:50:29,525
it's an amazing shared experience,

999
00:50:29,525 --> 00:50:30,406
which we all talk about.

1000
00:50:30,406 --> 00:50:32,708
So the sharing part,

1001
00:50:32,708 --> 00:50:34,389
the everybody seeing the same thing part,

1002
00:50:34,389 --> 00:50:35,330
is really, really important.

1003
00:50:36,412 --> 00:50:39,094
We've been dreaming about this at Niantic.

1004
00:50:39,094 --> 00:50:41,077
Our designers and artists have the things

1005
00:50:41,077 --> 00:50:42,518
that we want to build.

1006
00:50:42,518 --> 00:50:45,842
We imagine our festivals with real life gems

1007
00:50:45,842 --> 00:50:47,664
and Pokéstops that everybody can see

1008
00:50:47,664 --> 00:50:49,266
and understand together.

1009
00:50:49,266 --> 00:50:50,947
Even going back to the early days of Ingress,

1010
00:50:50,947 --> 00:50:52,329
we were thinking about this.

1011
00:50:53,132 --> 00:50:59,578
More recently, we've been thinking about non-game applications and what these kinds of holograms can do.

1012
00:50:59,578 --> 00:51:07,165
The technology is not there yet, but I think you saw from the preceding section that we are getting closer.

1013
00:51:07,165 --> 00:51:10,949
This is an example of one of those baby steps forward.

1014
00:51:10,949 --> 00:51:17,655
So, this is a project that we did with our colleagues and partners, SoftBank in Japan.

1015
00:51:18,820 --> 00:51:21,441
It's done on HoloLens 1, not HoloLens 2.

1016
00:51:21,441 --> 00:51:26,083
And we actually captured this footage

1017
00:51:26,083 --> 00:51:27,504
at the top of Roppongi Hills.

1018
00:51:27,504 --> 00:51:28,964
I don't know if anybody's been to Tokyo,

1019
00:51:28,964 --> 00:51:30,345
but probably some of you have,

1020
00:51:30,345 --> 00:51:31,685
and you know the big skyscraper.

1021
00:51:31,685 --> 00:51:33,146
So when you see this,

1022
00:51:33,146 --> 00:51:35,047
imagine you're on the top floor of the skyscraper.

1023
00:51:35,047 --> 00:51:37,167
We're gonna look out the window in a second,

1024
00:51:37,167 --> 00:51:38,128
you'll understand why.

1025
00:51:39,837 --> 00:51:42,540
So as we look around the room, we're seeing,

1026
00:51:42,540 --> 00:51:45,083
and everybody who comes through the experience,

1027
00:51:45,083 --> 00:51:46,684
we ran a bunch of people through this,

1028
00:51:46,684 --> 00:51:49,688
everybody saw the same things in the same location,

1029
00:51:49,688 --> 00:51:52,791
so they were shared experiences, as I was talking about.

1030
00:51:52,791 --> 00:51:58,116
We had specific Pokemon inhabiting certain parts

1031
00:51:58,116 --> 00:52:00,599
of this pretty open room.

1032
00:52:03,870 --> 00:52:11,534
And then when you walked out to the window and looked out across the city, you could actually see all the Pokemon gems where they're supposed to be.

1033
00:52:11,534 --> 00:52:17,577
We can see our legendary birds flying through the air. I think Moltres is in the background.

1034
00:52:20,138 --> 00:52:24,721
So it was really exciting for us because it was one of those glimpses of the future.

1035
00:52:24,721 --> 00:52:26,923
You know, you can only do this in a limited way.

1036
00:52:26,923 --> 00:52:30,926
You can prototype under certain conditions.

1037
00:52:30,926 --> 00:52:34,449
But it is a glimpse of what's going to be possible in the not-too-distant future.

1038
00:52:34,449 --> 00:52:36,991
Okay, so I want to wrap this up.

1039
00:52:36,991 --> 00:52:40,454
I think we're getting close to time.

1040
00:52:40,454 --> 00:52:45,077
So we've talked about AR and we've talked about...

1041
00:52:45,691 --> 00:52:48,012
the history and the things that we've learned.

1042
00:52:48,012 --> 00:52:51,314
We've talked about the technology that we're building.

1043
00:52:51,314 --> 00:52:55,276
And last, we talked about some of the product potential.

1044
00:52:55,276 --> 00:52:57,176
And I think for you product designers and game creators

1045
00:52:57,176 --> 00:52:58,937
out there, your mind is, you probably

1046
00:52:58,937 --> 00:53:01,318
have 1,000 ideas of stuff that you would like to build.

1047
00:53:02,714 --> 00:53:03,974
So whenever people ask that question,

1048
00:53:03,974 --> 00:53:09,257
well where is AR in the sort of hype cycle or whatever?

1049
00:53:09,257 --> 00:53:11,718
Is it up, is it down?

1050
00:53:11,718 --> 00:53:13,259
I don't really care about that.

1051
00:53:13,259 --> 00:53:17,241
The question that's interesting is,

1052
00:53:17,241 --> 00:53:22,964
is it something that is meaningful with a capital M?

1053
00:53:22,964 --> 00:53:26,746
Like is it something that's gonna affect our lives

1054
00:53:26,746 --> 00:53:27,587
in a significant way,

1055
00:53:27,587 --> 00:53:30,388
in many people's lives in a significant way?

1056
00:53:31,280 --> 00:53:33,782
And I absolutely believe that it is.

1057
00:53:33,782 --> 00:53:36,964
You know, what is happening on handsets today is a warmup.

1058
00:53:36,964 --> 00:53:38,605
That's the pregame.

1059
00:53:38,605 --> 00:53:40,887
What's going to happen with glasses in the future

1060
00:53:40,887 --> 00:53:41,268
is the real deal.

1061
00:53:41,268 --> 00:53:45,491
But I think it's one of those platform shifts.

1062
00:53:46,616 --> 00:53:48,797
you see it once every 10 or 20 years.

1063
00:53:48,797 --> 00:53:51,538
You know, and I've lived through a couple.

1064
00:53:51,538 --> 00:53:54,820
We saw PCs, we saw the cloud, we saw mobile.

1065
00:53:54,820 --> 00:53:56,100
I think AR is one of those shifts.

1066
00:53:56,100 --> 00:53:58,922
So it's something that I think is worth our time

1067
00:53:58,922 --> 00:53:59,542
to understand.

1068
00:53:59,542 --> 00:54:03,063
It's worth our time and money to invest early in.

1069
00:54:03,063 --> 00:54:05,364
And I think it's gonna be hugely important.

1070
00:54:05,364 --> 00:54:07,165
Rose colored glasses, I wanna touch on that.

1071
00:54:07,165 --> 00:54:08,746
That was part of the title of the talk.

1072
00:54:08,746 --> 00:54:11,887
People have knocked AR because they've said,

1073
00:54:13,740 --> 00:54:16,741
Oh, I didn't switch my slide to the beautiful closing slide here.

1074
00:54:16,741 --> 00:54:17,901
Perfect, rose-colored glasses.

1075
00:54:17,901 --> 00:54:20,242
So some people have said, hey, I always like rose-colored glasses.

1076
00:54:20,242 --> 00:54:21,742
You're taking it away from the world.

1077
00:54:21,742 --> 00:54:24,403
People aren't seeing the world as it really is.

1078
00:54:24,403 --> 00:54:25,543
So it's a bad thing.

1079
00:54:25,543 --> 00:54:28,884
I want to push back on that a little bit.

1080
00:54:28,884 --> 00:54:32,225
A good pair of sunglasses, if it's bright outside,

1081
00:54:32,225 --> 00:54:35,185
they actually don't get in your way of seeing the world.

1082
00:54:35,185 --> 00:54:36,706
They help you see the world more clearly.

1083
00:54:36,706 --> 00:54:37,886
They eliminate the glare.

1084
00:54:37,886 --> 00:54:38,366
You can focus.

1085
00:54:38,366 --> 00:54:40,467
You can see things you couldn't otherwise see.

1086
00:54:41,679 --> 00:54:43,381
And that's how I think of AR.

1087
00:54:43,381 --> 00:54:44,982
We're adding things to the world,

1088
00:54:44,982 --> 00:54:50,046
but the things that we can add can deepen our appreciation

1089
00:54:50,046 --> 00:54:53,389
for the world and our understanding of the world.

1090
00:54:53,389 --> 00:54:58,113
I think there are two primary things

1091
00:54:58,113 --> 00:55:00,095
that AR can do for us.

1092
00:55:00,095 --> 00:55:03,998
One is it can allow us to see the world in a fresh way

1093
00:55:03,998 --> 00:55:06,901
by causing us to pause and seeing history.

1094
00:55:07,762 --> 00:55:10,842
everything that's interesting about the world brought forward to us.

1095
00:55:10,842 --> 00:55:15,464
I really think there's an opportunity to deepen our connection with the places that we live.

1096
00:55:15,464 --> 00:55:19,465
The second thing that I think is incredibly important about that

1097
00:55:19,465 --> 00:55:23,526
is that it allows us to do it in a shared way and to have experiences together,

1098
00:55:23,526 --> 00:55:28,788
to have these adventures in real life with our friends, with our family, and with our kids.

1099
00:55:28,788 --> 00:55:31,428
And by deepening our connection with community...

1100
00:55:32,456 --> 00:55:34,839
in the physical sense, and deepening our connection

1101
00:55:34,839 --> 00:55:37,122
with community in the meeting our neighbors

1102
00:55:37,122 --> 00:55:39,685
and doing stuff together with our friends sense,

1103
00:55:39,685 --> 00:55:42,389
I think is a really important step forward for technology.

1104
00:55:42,389 --> 00:55:44,571
And frankly, I think it's something that we need.

1105
00:55:44,571 --> 00:55:47,715
I think it's something that the world needs.

1106
00:55:48,061 --> 00:55:49,462
You've seen how it can go wrong.

1107
00:55:49,462 --> 00:55:51,382
So thank you, Keiichi, for showing us

1108
00:55:51,382 --> 00:55:54,183
how horribly wrong AR could go.

1109
00:55:54,183 --> 00:55:58,865
But I believe that the positives here outweigh that.

1110
00:55:58,865 --> 00:56:00,726
And I want to put it to everybody here.

1111
00:56:00,726 --> 00:56:02,306
There's a Gandhi quote, which is,

1112
00:56:02,306 --> 00:56:04,287
be the change you want to see in the world.

1113
00:56:04,287 --> 00:56:07,508
In our professional lives, I think the quote is,

1114
00:56:07,508 --> 00:56:11,130
it is really up to us to build the future

1115
00:56:11,130 --> 00:56:13,030
that we want to live in.

1116
00:56:14,157 --> 00:56:16,720
It's up to us to build the future that we want to live in,

1117
00:56:16,720 --> 00:56:17,821
that we want to exist.

1118
00:56:17,821 --> 00:56:20,545
And more importantly, it's up to us to build a future

1119
00:56:20,545 --> 00:56:22,887
that we want our kids to live in.

1120
00:56:22,887 --> 00:56:25,730
So if you guys are inspired by the opportunity here

1121
00:56:25,730 --> 00:56:27,873
and are interested in AR, reach out to us.

1122
00:56:27,873 --> 00:56:29,154
We have a contest.

1123
00:56:29,154 --> 00:56:31,537
We're looking for allies.

1124
00:56:31,537 --> 00:56:32,558
But there's a lot of work to do

1125
00:56:32,558 --> 00:56:34,140
and I think it's important work.

1126
00:56:34,140 --> 00:56:34,861
Thank you.

